    {
      "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-8013-bbd6-ef04dc07d3f8",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Around 30% of students that are registered in the first year do not return for the second. The authors take a step to understand why by analyzing data from the University of Washington. Authors find that it is possible to identify early predictors and, not only that, that it is also possible to predict dropout when a single term of academic data (end of first-semester equivalent). ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-8013-bbd6-ef04dc07d3f8",
        "parent": {
